{"word":"συνείρω","slug":"συνείρω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>συνείρω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> and <a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to string together</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>connectere</el>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to string</i> words <i>together</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>: then, seemingly <a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> (<a href='S:subaudi, subaudito'>sub.</a> <el>λόγους</el>) <i>to speak on and on, go on without pausing</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}